tellraw @s {"text":"\n-------------- Rauchergames Setup Guide --------------","color":"green"}
tellraw @s {"text":"\nLong Version:","color":"green"}
tellraw @s [{"text":"Overwiew: ","color":"light_purple"},{"text":"Rauchergames (don't ask about the name) consists of, so far, 4 game modes (plus one for testing), that are all played with up to 12 players divided into 2 teams (while it is possible to play alone, at least 2 players per team are recommended). Each player can choose from one of 7 kits with unique stats and abilities. Win by completing the game mode-specific objective. Make sure you have the Rauch Texturepack installed.","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"\nStarting Out: ","color":"light_purple"},{"text":"If this is the first time the datapack is active, you wil be asked to set the lobby position. The lobby is the place players return to after a game. With the spawn egg, right click on the block at the desired location. If you somehow lose the item, simply reload the world (","color":"yellow"},{"text":"/reload","color":"gold","hoverEvent":{"action":"show_text","contents":[{"text":"Click to Suggest Command"}]},"clickEvent":{"action":"suggest_command","value":"/reload"}},{"text":").","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"\nAdmins: ","color":"light_purple"},{"text":"In order to play, you first need to add a map. To edit game settings, add maps etc. you need to be an admin. You can become an admin using the command (","color":"yellow"},{"text":"/tag NAME add admin","hoverEvent":{"action":"show_text","contents":[{"text":"Click to Suggest Command"}]},"clickEvent":{"action":"suggest_command","value":"/tag NAME add admin"},"color":"gold"},{"text":"). You can do this with every player you want, however they also need rights on the server (permission level 2 or more). To remove admin rights, do (","color":"yellow"},{"text":"/tag NAME remove admin","hoverEvent":{"action":"show_text","contents":[{"text":"Click to Suggest Command"}]},"clickEvent":{"action":"suggest_command","value":"/tag NAME remove admin"},"color":"gold"},{"text":"). Admins have access to the \"Settings\" Book in their first hotbar slot. From here you can change game modes, maps and more.","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"\nAdding a Map: ","color":"light_purple"},{"text":" Add a map by going to the 3rd page of the \"Settings\" Book and clicking on \"Add Map\". A Guide will be available there, too.","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"\nKits: ","color":"light_purple"},{"text":"Before starting, each player has to select a kit using the book called \"Kit Selector / Settings\". You can see their stats and abilities by hovering over the name. Click to select. Each class has three abilities, R, Q and F. In game, you can activate R by right-clicking and Q and F by pressing the respective key on your keyboard. All abilities have a cooldown.","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"\nGame Modes: ","color":"light_purple"},{"text":"You can choose a game mode using the \"Settings\" Book. Hovering over the name will show information about the mode.","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"\nStarting a Game: ","color":"light_purple"},{"text":"After having selected a kit and a map (using the 2nd page of the \"Settings\"-Book), right-click with the green item called \"Join Queue\" to join the queue. Here all players can choose a team (players that don't pick will be evenly distributed). Note that there is nothing stopping unbalanced teams :). Admins can start the game using either the chosen teams or random teams. Make sure everyone that wants to play is in queue before starting.","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"\nAborting a Game: ","color":"light_purple"},{"text":"If you want to abort a game, the easiest way to do that is to type ","color":"yellow"},{"text":"/function rauch:game/add/stats/tie","hoverEvent":{"action":"show_text","contents":[{"text":"Click to Suggest Command"}]},"clickEvent":{"action":"suggest_command","value":"/function rauch:game/add/stats/tie"},"color":"gold"}]
tellraw @s {"text":"\nShort Version:","color":"green"}
tellraw @s [{"text":"1. Make sure you have the texture pack installed","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"2. Place Lobby Position (Spawn Egg)","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"3. Type ","color":"yellow"},{"text":"/tag ","color":"gold","hoverEvent":{"action":"show_text","contents":[{"text":"Click to Suggest Command"}]},"clickEvent":{"action":"suggest_command","value":"/tag @s add admin"}},{"selector":"@s","color":"gold","hoverEvent":{"action":"show_text","contents":[{"text":"Click to Suggest Command"}]},"clickEvent":{"action":"suggest_command","value":"/tag @s add admin"}},{"text":" add admin","color":"gold","hoverEvent":{"action":"show_text","contents":[{"text":"Click to Suggest Command"}]},"clickEvent":{"action":"suggest_command","value":"/tag @s add admin"}},{"text":" to become an admin","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"4. Add a map (3rd page of \"Settings\" Book)","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"5. Select a map (2nd page of \"Settings\" Book)","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"6. Select a game mode (1st page of \"Settings\" Book)","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"7. Everyone has to select a kit","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"8. Everyone that wants to play has to join the queue","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s [{"text":"9. An admin has to start the game","color":"yellow"}]
tellraw @s {"text":"------------------- Setup Guide End -------------------","color":"green"}
